[This report adds little that we didn't know already but the Queensland Biosecurity folk have gone through their records to determine how many livestock have died from anthrax, 153, and not as thought originally from toxic pimelea plants. If there are historic livestock anthrax burial sites, they have discovered the hard way in Australia that leveling a field, to facilitate better irrigation and grazing for example, can result in spreading spores from those old graves onto the soil surface. To get around this risk the Russians found it was wise to grow forage crops for a couple of years to allow any spores to die before allowing grazing. - Mod.MHJ

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Dirranbandi, Queensland, Australia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5941123,64162]
